Entries.default: "Perhaps it should have a whale head instead."
"The oldest work of kith lasts but a blink against the depthless void of eternity."
"Strange, ja, to see such ice north of Naasitaq?"
"I always thought of the Beast as having four legs."
"An aurochs, yes. But with the torso of a man."
"Exact - wait, what say? How can god have torso of man and body of aurochs?"
"All things end, but some endings are more glorious than others."
"There, then gone, sculptor and sculpture alike."
"It fills me with the night's song."
"He is a god. He can be anything."
